.TH ypmake 1M "17 Aug 2006" "SunOS 5.11" "System Administration Commands"
.SH NAME
ypmake \- rebuild NIS database
.SH SYNOPSIS
.LP
.nf
\fBcd\fR \fB/var/yp\fR ; \fBmake\fR [\fImap\fR]
.fi

.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
.LP
The file called
.B Makefile
in
.B /var/yp
is used by
.BR make (1S)
to build the  Network Information Service (\fBNIS\fR) database. With no
arguments,
.B make
creates
.B dbm
databases for any
.B NIS
maps
that are out-of-date, and then executes \fByppush\fR(1M) to notify slave
databases that there has been a change.
.sp
.LP
If you supply a
.I map
on the command line,
.B make
will update that
map only. Typing
.B "make passwd"
will create and
.B yppush
the password
database (assuming it is out of date). Likewise,
.B "make ipnodes"
and
.B make networks
will create and
.B yppush
the
.B ipnodes
and
.B network
files,
.B $(INETDIR)/ipnodes
and
.BR $(DIR)/networks .
.sp
.LP
There are four special variables used by
.BR make :
.BR DIR ,
which gives
the directory of the source files;
.BR NOPUSH ,
which when non-null
inhibits doing a
.B yppush
of the new database files;
.BR INETDIR ,
which gives the directory of the
.B ipnodes
source file; and
.BR DOM ,
which is used to construct a domain other than the master's default domain.
The default for
.B DIR
is
.BR /etc ,
and the default for
.BR INETDIR
is
.BR /etc/inet .
The default for
.B NOPUSH
is the null string.
.sp
.LP
Refer to
.BR ypfiles (4)
and \fBypserv\fR(1M) for an overview of the
.B NIS
service.
.sp
.LP
If a
.B NIS
to LDAP (N2L) configuration file,
.BR /var/yp/NISLDAPmapping ,
is present, the
.B NIS
server components
run in N2L mode. In N2L mode, the server components use a new set of map
files with an LDAP-prefix, based on the LDAP DIT. In N2L mode, authoritative
NIS information is obtained from the DIT. The NIS source files and
.B ypmake
have no role, and they should not be used. If
.B ypmake
is
accidentally run, then the server components will detect this, and will log
a warning message. For additional information, see
.BR ypfiles (4).
